HEADWORD: Tipster
<hw>Tip"ster</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Tip</ets> a
hint + <ets>-ster</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who makes a practice of giving
or selling tips, or private hints or information, esp. for use in
gambling upon the probable outcome of events, as horse races.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

